61.6	Drawing	Drawing	Drawing is a form of visual art that makes use of any number of drawing instruments to mark a two-dimensional medium. Common instruments include graphite pencils, pen and ink, inked brushes, wax color pencils, crayons, charcoal, chalk, pastels, markers, styluses, and various metals (such as silverpoint). An artist who practices or works in drawing may be called a draughtsman or draftsman.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/db/Rembrandt-A-Lion-Lying-Down-207063_detail.jpg/320px-Rembrandt-A-Lion-Lying-Down-207063_detail.jpg
